ientific? Is organic farming? After centuries of disputes like these, Gieryn finds no stable criteria that absolutely distinguish science from non-science. Science remains a pliable cultural space, flexibly reshaped to claim credibility for some beliefs while denying it to others. In a timely epilogue, Gieryn finds this same controversy at the heart of the raging "science wars."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aCross-cultural studies. 0aSciencevCross-cultural studies. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 0aSciencexSocial aspects. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226824420423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226824420/original  a978-3-11-066785-1  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aGBV-deGruyter-alles